<div class="sg-h1">Helpers</div>
<div class="sg-note sg-note--outdent">Helpers are a bunch of classes to apply very common styles e.g. make text right aligned, apply the base bottom margin to an element, etc. They're used arbitrarily i.e. only if an element/module doesn't already have a class to which you could apply this styling.</div>

<!-- Spacing -->
<div class="sg-h2">Spacing</div>
<div class="sg-note">To apply spacing via the base bottom margin or variants of it e.g. half / double apply any of the: <code class="sg-code">class="mrg-base"</code>, <code class="sg-code">class="mrg-half"</code>, or <code class="sg-code">class="mrg-dbl"</code> helper classes to the element, can also apply 'top' margins by adding 'top' to the end of the aformentioned classes e.g. <code class="sg-code">class="mrg-dbl--top"</code>, or to remove spacing applied via margins apply any of the <code class="sg-code">class="flush--"</code> helper classes.</div>

<div class="sg-h3">Apply Spacing</div>
<div class="sg-h4">Bottom</div>
<p class="mrg-base">I'm applying the base bottom margin.</p>
<p class="mrg-half">I'm applying half of the base bottom margin.</p>
<p class="mrg-dbl">I'm applying double the base bottom margin.</p>
<div class="sg-h4">Top</div>
<p class="mrg-base--top flush--btm">I'm applying the base top margin.</p>
<p class="mrg-half--top flush--btm">I'm applying half of the base top margin.</p>
<p class="mrg-dbl--top flush--btm">I'm applying double the base top margin.</p>

<div class="sg-h3">Remove Spacing (Flush)</div>
<p class="flush">I have no spacing (margin).</p>
<p class="flush--top">I have no top spacing (margin).</p>
<p class="flush--right">I have no right spacing (margin).</p>
<p class="flush--btm">I have no bottom spacing (margin).</p>
<p class="flush--left">I have no left spacing (margin).</p>
<p class="flush--ends">I have no end (top/bottom) spacing (margin).</p>
<p class="flush--sides">I have no side (left/right) spacing (margin).</p>
<!-- //Spacing -->

<!-- Float -->
<div class="sg-h2">Float</div>
<div class="sg-note">Any element that receives the <code class="sg-code">class="float-left"</code> or <code class="sg-code">class="float-right"</code> helper classes will be floated to the left or right. To remove float altogether apply the <code class="sg-code">class="float-none"</code> helper class.</div>

